			"text": "Gigatitan was a genus of titanopteran insect that lived during the Middle to Late Triassic in what is now the Madygen Formation of Kyrgyzstan. Like most titanopterans, it was a mantis-like predator that caught smaller prey using its enlarged, spiny forelimbs. Despite its large wings, its relatively heavy weight may have limited it to gliding rather than truly \"flying\"."
